Text.Value: Now come, be witness as your father names me the first Archduke of Baldur's Gate.
Now come, be witness as I make history as the first Archduke of Baldur's Gate.
Exquisite timing. Dearest patriars, but a moment. Lord Enver Gortash at your service.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [GERRY] Gortash strides towards the player from idle position left foot forward (down stairs - 5 steps) going from Stage 01 to Stage 03. Line to be delivered as he theatrically walks down the stairs - last line to be delivered in front of the player (GortashStridesDownstairsVersion01)
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gortash looks to player and smiles wide. He speaks to the room gesturing his arms enthusiastically while walking down the stairs to get closer to the player. First line is addressed to the room and second line is addressed to the player.

Text.Value: Stand with Bhaal, or it will spell your doom. But I can offer some aid for the storm you are about to weather.
Now, now, Karlach, let's not be hasty. We've begun something far greater than that temper of yours. You have a Netherstone. That bears discussion.
Hold your tongue. This horde could bring even a mounted kith'rak to her knees.

EditorData.NodeContext: Aside to player

Text.Value: Ah - and my old friend Karlach. It's no wonder your victory was so decisive. How have you been, darling?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Staging 01 - Reference

Text.Value: *Doubt casts a shadow on your mind. You've little chance to best Gortash's Steel Watchers.*
I want to avenge myself. I want to strike at Orin.
Bhaal isn't done with you, you must know that. You have effortless talents, killing instinctually like you breathe blood.
Say nothing.
Orin is... slippery, shall we say. She even eluded my Steel Watch - before you destroyed it.
Don't. You'll only invite his ire. And your own death.

EditorData.NodeContext: telepathic, Emperor not physically present (speaking directly into player's head)

Text.Value: This is the first step towards our glory. I really must insist.

EditorData.logicalname: Dark Urge, did not refuse alliance

Text.Value: I'm not interested in bargaining with the likes of you.
A shame.
You make me sick.
I knew I'd meet Ketheric's slayer eventually, but I had no idea it was you, Karlach.
When it finishes executing its current orders, it will be free to do as it wishes. That would be bad for everyone.
Father. No!
My master admires you, as I always have. For the slaughter you bring, and for the Netherstones you bear.
Tread carefully. Remember, you must do what it takes to survive. Even if it means striking a deal with the enemy.
Oh, but I most certainly am not.
Silence can be an excellent tool, you know. Especially if it spares you an unwinnable fight.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'Please don't cause a scene/pick a fight we can't win' Aside to player

Text.Value: Don't look at me. And don't you dare look at Boo.

EditorData.NodeContext: Player looking to him after being told there's a shapeshifter among us. First line is shrugged, nonchalant. Second line is genuinely offended, mildly aghast that it might even occur to us

Text.Value: This isn't going to end well. Mark my words.
You're awfully friendly for the man who sold me to a devil ten years ago.
First, Orin the Red, bloody dagger of Bhaal, causes panic in the streets through killings in the Absolute's name.
*Gortash's mind remains unknown to you.*

Text.Value: I have no interest in this sham of a ceremony.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Staging 04 - Reference

Text.Value: Ah! My dear friend, what a brilliant child you've been to your Father. It must feel good to be the favourite. Orin must still be screaming in the Hells.
You are mistaken if you think I can control myself.
I am ending this here, consequences be damned.
You are soon to witness the people of Baldur's Gate granting me complete power over them. All out of fear of the Absolute.
Such pluck! How I admire it. Alas, I take unkindly to threats - no matter how hollow.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Camera moves in on a nearby Steel Watcher automaton.

Text.Value: Then we proceed. The patriars await.
Once it is freed from its shackles, I doubt we'll ever be able to bring it under control again.
What do you propose?
My friends. The Steel Watch stands ready. Let its blade fall on any who would diminish our city!

EditorData.AnimationTags: [GERRY] Gortash stands pleased and turns to player and smiles taking a few steps beyond the player.,
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He speaks his arms enthusiastically. Addressed to the crowd.  Gortash stands pleased and turns right 180 to player and smiles.
EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken to all attendees of the ceremony.

Text.Value: Time flies, doesn't it? But never mind that - we have much to discuss. You have a Netherstone. That makes us allies.
And you are: a marvel. You've brought Ketheric to his knees and made Orin grovel.
Swearest thou true faith and fealty to the same, by word, deed, and decree, so that none may suffer?

EditorData.AnimationTags: [GERRY] Ravenguard move to top of the blade from Gortash left shoulder to his right shoulder. Gortadsh is still kneeling looking down (looping idle),
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Ravenguard move to top of the blade from Gortash left shoulder to his right shoulder. Gortadsh is still kneeling looking down (looping idle)

Text.Value: Then allow me to pique it for you.
It was all going so well - until you vanished. Orin informed us that henceforth she would speak for the temple of Bhaal, and act on their behalf.
But - my stars! That can't be my old friend Karlach, can it? How long has it been? Five years? Six? I'm delighted to see you again.
Be that as it may, you will sit quietly and watch as history is made.
I'd rather juice my own eyes.
And so begins your tyranny.
The faithful will do anything in the name of their god.
Dearest patriars, dearest Ravengard, but a moment. The Blade of Frontiers graces our halls - and he's wearing his devilish best.
Dearest patriars, dearest Ravengard, but a moment. The Blade of Frontiers graces our halls.
So unite we did. First we obtained the crown; then we enslaved the brain. From there, it was but a small step to the most successful religious hoax ever perpetrated.
The Bhaal Temple, your old haunt, now reeks of her ichors.
Keep quiet.
What kind of understanding do you suggest?
You misread me. I've come to end this evil plot.
The Steel Watch appreciate your cooperation, citizen.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The Watcher stays menacing, ready to attack.
EditorData.NodeContext: Gets new command after starting to engage. Gortash sends a remote command to let the player through.

Text.Value: Farewell.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Contingency node if we need to add extra lines

Text.Value: Your camp is compromised. One among you is an impostor. A Faceless.
Nod.
Perhaps.
An ally could be useful, at least for now. And when he's no longer useful - well, we can dispose of him then.
You should know better than most, Karlach, the risks of falling out of my favour.
A doppelganger - hidden among us? Tsk'va!

EditorData.NodeContext: Tsk'va! - tsk-VA! Shit!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Staging 03 - Reference

Text.Value: I swear.

EditorData.NodeContext: Gortadsh is still kneeling looking down.

Text.Value: In short - you can trust me.
You've met her assassins. Efficient killers by all accounts. I know you survived previous encounters. But she won't relent.
What a shame to refuse the power of a god.
Indeed you are. Look at you - cold-blooded as ever.
What kind of partnership do you have in mind?
Next, I - we - will declare curfew and begin infecting the masses. Our subjects will hear the voice of their Absolute god.
Karlach! My dear, aren't you a sight for sore eyes. How long has it been? Five years? Six? I'm delighted to see you again.
What does the cult of the Absolute have to do with this?
Ask the Emperor: Is he telling the truth?
Stop this. Gortash and Ravengard are with the Absolute!
Go fuck yourself, Gortash.
*You look carefully but discover nothing.*
Don't - we'd face very poor odds if you start a fight now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Aside to player

Text.Value: Enver Gortash. Swearest thou, by Balduran's blade, to defend the citizens of Baldur's Gate from enemies within and without?

Text.Value: 'Together'? You've got to be joking.
We'll catch up once we've covered more pressing matters - Thorm's Netherstone, more to the point.
The likes of you stand to benefit from the likes of me.
Gathered guests, grant ye consent?

EditorData.NodeContext: Ravenguard is in loop idle weapon pointing down.

Text.Value: As allies, it seems none of you can be trusted. You, Orin, Ketheric.
You would have carried out that part of the plan, at least, had Orin not ruined your hard work.
They knew this would only work if we stood united and coordinated our powers.
Lord Enver Gortash, the people cry your name. Will you -

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to room and then to Gortash as part of speech gesturing his arms enthusiastically.

Text.Value: I will bring her to heel.
Take that with a grain of salt. This is Gortash we're talking to.
What do you say? Shall we be allies?

Lord Enver Gortash at your service.

Text.Value: Even horror has a home. Find her nest, and slay her there.
Hold your tongue. Gortash and his allies could bring even a mounted kith'rak to her knees.

Text.Value: Aggressive action will not be tolerated in the presence of the patriars of this proud city.

Text.Value: Let's make our pact anew. A divine oath, sworn upon spirit and flesh. I do no harm to you, nor you to me.
I am ending this here, consequences be damned.
Father...

Text.Value: What are you getting at?
Perhaps she and I can be allies.
Fine. Let's get it over with.
Correct your tone, citizen.

Text.Value: You carry the stone plucked from Myrkul's Chosen, besides. Why call you 'enemy' when I could repair an old friendship?
There is an old wisdom: a brittle alliance can never be mended - it can only break.
With Ketheric gone, Orin proved treacherous. Bhaal's Chosen wants the Netherstones for herself.
All right.
'Let's be allies,' said the viper to the frog.

Synopsis:
Ceremony of Gortash becoming the Grand Duke.
The start of the dialog depends on whether Steel Watchers are enabled (present) or not.
In the dialog Gortash tells you to kill Orin and then concludes the ceremony. Player can attack but it would be very hard to win.
